trend_summary: From earliest to latest images, the suburban zone shows steady infill. Small vacant lots become housing, warehouse blocks expand near the highway interchange, and several new parking areas appear. Road layout is largely unchanged, while tree cover slightly rises as street-side planting matures. Overall, growth is modest, keeping a green, medium-density suburban character.
notable_changes: Expansion of light-industrial/warehouse roofs in the southwest corner near the highway.
Several cul-de-sac infill housing clusters replace open grass lots across central neighborhoods.
New commercial plaza with large parking lot emerges along the main north-south arterial.
Slight increase in tree canopy and backyard vegetation across residential blocks.
Addition of highway slip-road and reconfigured interchange lanes on the northern edge.
